These are all the functions I used to make a failed Kalman Filter tracking of the ball. 
The main reason this sucks is that it want's measurements as somewhere with guassian like uncertainty
BUT our detection scome as points that are highly spacially separated, so there isn't a good way to write that
gaussian uncertainty. 
You should just need the file path of a video, 
and then run all the code in tennis_ball_kalman_tracker_with_extractor.ipynb
